    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top, tail, peel and finely dice your<strong> carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>leek[s]</strong> thoroughly to remove any grit from between the leaves, then top, tail and slice finely</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-haddock-leek-and-potato-chowder/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pot (with a matching lid) with a large knob of<strong> butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>diced carrot</strong> and <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>leek</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-haddock-leek-and-potato-chowder/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a full kettle</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-haddock-leek-and-potato-chowder/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-haddock-leek-and-potato-chowder/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> in 550ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[700ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [950ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-haddock-leek-and-potato-chowder/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the\u00a0leek has softened, add your\u00a0<strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>ground\u00a0turmeric</strong>\u00a0and 1 tsp\u00a0<span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong>\u00a0and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Add the<strong> stock</strong>\u00a0and\u00a0<strong>chopped potatoes</strong>\u00a0and cook for 15-18 min or until the potatoes are almost fork-tender</p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-haddock-leek-and-potato-chowder/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the\u00a0potatoes<strong> </strong>are almost fork-tender, add your\u00a0<strong>haddock bites </strong>(unevenly sized haddock bites? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!), <strong>spinach</strong>\u00a0and <strong>soft\u00a0cheese</strong> to the potatoes and season with a pinch of\u00a0<strong>salt</strong>\u00a0and\u00a0<strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Cook, covered, for 4-5 min or until the\u00a0haddock\u00a0is cooked through and the potatoes are fork-tender \u2013 this is your <strong>curried\u00a0haddock, leek &\u00a0potato chowder</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-haddock-leek-and-potato-chowder/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>curried\u00a0haddock, leek &\u00a0potato chowder</strong></p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
